From d50cf07b51b271df05dfb447fcd6c6e80a35dedb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Amir Patel <amirpate@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Sep 2025 00:01:20 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:DP:wifi:ath12k: Remove rcu lock while updating peer
 stats

In current implementation, during stats update from monitor path,
while accessing peer, rcu lock is acquired and then spinlock is acquired,
but as spinlock is acquired, rcu lock is not needed.
Morover as stats update is happening in WQ, rcu lock may get acquired
and preempted by softirq, this can lead to rcu stall.

to address this, remove rcu lock during peer stats update from
monitor path.

Patch-dependency : None

Fixes: Idd214a7c81e ("pkg upgrade Added subsys, ath11k and ath12k
       patches for win.wlan_host_opensource.4.0")

Change-Id: Ic1bbcf2c55d5dfa9dc3c0c051e9ee4de6e91f0f2
Signed-off-by: Amir Patel <amirpate@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_mon2.c | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_mon2.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_mon2.c
index 81d5818..feb6187 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_mon2.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/dp_mon2.c
@@ -1359,7 +1359,6 @@ ath12k_wifi7_dp_mon_rx_process_ppdu(struct work_struct *work)
 			if (filter_category == DP_MPDU_FILTER_CATEGORY_MO)
 				goto free_buf;

-			rcu_read_lock();
 			spin_lock_bh(&dp->dp_lock);

 			if (!list_empty(&dp->neighbor_peers)) {
@@ -1409,7 +1408,6 @@ ath12k_wifi7_dp_mon_rx_process_ppdu(struct work_struct *work)

 unlock:
 			spin_unlock_bh(&dp->dp_lock);
-			rcu_read_unlock();
 free_buf:
 			page_frag_free(status_desc->mon_buf);
 			mon_stats->status_buf_free++;
--
2.34.1

